ity policies through the lens of order and disorder-provides a clearer understanding, generally, of how cities work (and why they sometimes do not), and specifically, of what disorder is and how it affects city life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCity planning and redevelopment lawzUnited States. 0aLand subdivisionxLaw and legislationzUnited States. 0aPolice-community relationszUnited States. 7aLAW / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030012494140uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030015505140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300155051423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300155051/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY